# {{project_name}} — vibe-slides project guide

This file is read by the build agent (`/vibe-slides build`) every time the
deck is rendered. It records **project-specific style constraints** that
override or specialize the skill's defaults.

Copy this file into the project root as `vibe-slides.md`, then edit the
rules below to match what you want this specific deck to look and feel
like.

Note: this file is **not** the project's `CLAUDE.md` — it is
vibe-slides-specific, so that dropping a deck project into an existing
repo does not collide with the repo's own `CLAUDE.md`.

---

## Theme

The theme lives at `theme.json`. It defines every color, font, and base
size used in the deck. When writing build.js, **never hardcode hex or
font names** — always go through `theme.color.*` and `theme.font.*`.

If a slide needs a color the theme doesn't provide, add it to theme.json
under a semantic name (e.g. `color.quoteBg`), don't inline the hex.

## Components

Registered components are listed in `components/_manifest.json`. Each has
documented params; respect them. If a slide needs a primitive that isn't
in the library, first consider whether it should become a new component.

## Style constraints — academic PPT defaults

These apply unless you override them below.

- **Tone:** calm, dense-but-breathable, evidence-first. No exclamation
  marks, no emojis.
- **Motion:** no animations, no transitions.
- **Gradients / effects:** disallowed. Flat fills only. The component
  library may use subtle shadows for depth (opacity ≤ 0.1); beyond that,
  avoid.
- **Accent discipline:** at most two accent colors on a single slide.
- **Typography hierarchy:** exactly one title per slide (size
  `theme.size.title`). Section headers inside a slide use
  `theme.size.section` or `h3`. Body text at `theme.size.body`.
- **Alignment:** left-align body text and lists. Center-align only
  titles, stat numbers, and single-line callouts.
- **Margins:** every element stays at least `theme.space.margin` from
  the slide edge unless it is an intentionally bleeding decorative
  shape.
- **No AI-tells:** do NOT draw accent lines beneath titles; do NOT use
  default blue; do NOT fill every inch of the slide.

## Motifs

Small, repeated visual choices the deck should commit to. The default is
`theme.motif` but you can strengthen or suppress here.

- Numbered circles for ordered steps and process flows.
- Left-edge accent bar on all "named" blocks (callouts, cards).
- A single thin gold stripe at the bottom of every content slide.

## Build conventions

- Slide size is driven by `theme.slide.w` / `theme.slide.h` — do not
  redefine layout in build.js.
- Put all slide functions side-by-side in one `build.js`; do not split
  across files. We're optimizing for readability over modularity.
- Use `addSlideTitle` and `addFooter` from
  `~/.claude/skills/vibe-slides/lib/render_helpers.js` for consistency.
- When a layout isn't obvious, fall back to a two-column split or a
  centered single column. Don't invent novel geometry without reason.

